AGENT-KITCHEN █
COOK | SERVE

─────────────────────

agent-kitchen is a second-order harness; it is a kitchen for the things that configure coding agents (skills, hooks, rules, CLAUDE.md, workflows).

It operates as dotfiles for your agent in the form of two plugins under a marketplace:

⛶ COOK makes the tools, tastes them, dates them, throws out what's gone stale.
⛶ SERVE is what's survived for me so far. It still tastes better than store-bought.

The kitchen is built on the idea that:

A frontier model in 2026 is very competent at most things, but its default in any domain is the competent average version of the thing. Getting it to do a specific, better version of the work you care about means refining its particularity and getting it very good in one specific way, against its own pull toward the middle of every distribution.

The artifacts here are commitments that try to drag a model off that median in a chosen direction. It works on the understanding that any tool that attempts to do this charges rent on future sessions and, as models continue to improve, is ultimately perishable. It is a practice of deciding what's worth pulling the model off its average for.

─────────────────────

COOK

⛶ FORGE: one triage ladder routes a behavior to the right surface (skill, hook, path-scoped rule, CLAUDE.md, workflow, subagent, MCP), with a stance that sets the bar each artifact has to clear.

⛶ HARNESS-AUDIT: inventories everything loaded at session start, counts the per-session token cost, and runs four checks: self-consistency, duplication across scopes, enforcement parity, scope discipline. built to remove things rather than add them.
 
⛶ HARVEST: mines session transcripts for the corrections the user had to make twice, dedups them against the standing harness, and hands survivors to the forge as earned-failure evidence.

⛶ INGEST: turns resources provided by the user into an artifact by fanning out one reader subagent per source, grounded in verbatim quotes.

─────────────────────

SERVE

⛶ My applied skills (an example of what COOK has produced that has survived several seasons of models and audits).

─────────────────────

STATE.md + HACKS.md are a verified snapshot of Claude Code's surfaces and lesser-known features, re-checked against the live changelog on each release.

─────────────────────

The harness in general:

⛶ Prices context before writing anything. Every artifact clears three bars: earned by a real failure or a real source; shifts attention in a way you can name; beats the model's default.

⛶ Tests if it's additive vs transformative. Does it save you typing, or change what's thinkable? Only the second kind earns its place.
 
⛶ Model-pins everything. Each artifact records the model, date, and version it was earned against.

⛶ Is optimized for subtraction to avoid rotting by accretion.
